{%- comment -%}
  Pickup badge snippet
  - Reads product metafield for shipping/pickup info (supports multiple keys)
  - Outputs a placeholder element with data attributes for client-side geolocation logic
  Expected metafields (optional, examples):
    product.metafields.shipping.ship_days
    product.metafields.custom.ship_days
    shop.metafields.store.pickup_coords ("lat,long")
  This snippet itself does not request geolocation; the client JS will request permission and update the badge.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- assign ship_days = product.metafields.shipping.ship_days
  | default: product.metafields.custom.ship_days
  | default: ''
-%}
{%- assign store_coords = shop.metafields.store.pickup_coords | default: '' -%}

<div
  class="product-pickup-badge js-pickup-badge"
  data-ship-days="{{ ship_days }}"
  data-store-coords="{{ store_coords }}"
  data-cutoff="15:30"
  data-timezone="America/Chicago"
  aria-live="polite"
>
  <!-- content injected by assets/pickup-badge.js -->
  <span class="visually-hidden">Pickup availability</span>
</div>
